  <static seed="1379" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalExpressionAlgebraSkills/addSubtractRationalExpressions10.pg">
    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{6r}{r+3}+\frac{18}{r+3}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>6, r\ne -3</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{6r}{r+3}+\frac{18}{r+3}} 
      \amp = \frac{{6r+18}}{{r+3}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{6\mathopen{}\left(r+3\right)}}{{r+3}} \\
      \amp = {6, r\ne -3}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>r+3</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {-3}</m>.</p>
</solution>
  </static>
